4 2. Board of trustees established. The Board of Trustees of the Cross Insurance Arena
5 is established to develop, review and make recommendations to the county commissioners
6 on financial, contractual and policy issues regarding the Cross Insurance Arena. The board
7 of trustees consists of 9 7 members appointed by the county commissioners as follows:
8 A. Two members from the City of Portland;
9 B. One member from each of the following sets of municipalities county commissioner
10 districts in Cumberland County:
11 (1) South Portland and Cape Elizabeth County Commissioner District 1;
12 (2) Scarborough, Westbrook and Falmouth County Commissioner District 2;
13 (3) Gorham, Windham, Standish, Baldwin and Sebago County Commissioner
14 District 3;
15 (4) Brunswick, Freeport, Harpswell, Pownal and New Gloucester County
16 Commissioner District 4; and
17 (5) Yarmouth, Cumberland, North Yarmouth, Gray, Casco, Raymond, Naples,
18 Harrison and Bridgton County Commissioner District 5; and
19 C. Two members at large.
20 Trustees are appointed for a term of 3 years and may not serve more than 2 consecutive
21 terms.
22 SUMMARY
2233 This bill changes in statute the geographical areas represented by members of the Board
2244 of Trustees of the Cross Insurance Arena from Portland and 5 sets of towns to the 5 county
2255 commissioner districts of Cumberland County.
